26/10/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Croatia's Ambassador to NATO Pjer Simunovic and Deputy Defence Minister Igor Pokaz submitted to NATO Tuesday (25 October) the fourth national Membership Action Plan for the period 2005-2006. The document outlines the priority tasks required to fulfil NATO political criteria, such as completing the refugee return process, accelerating judicial reforms, combating corruption and increasing the protection of minority rights. It also stresses Croatia's commitment to close the chapter on co-operation with The Hague tribunal by resolving the case of fugitive Ante Gotovina. (HRT - 25/10/05)
